data.enText: a branch of the Christian Church

data.chText: 基督教所有教派的人都出席了这次会议。
data.enText: Christians of all denominations attended the conference.
a unit of value, especially of money

data.chText: 各种面额的硬币和纸币
data.enText: coins and banknotes of various denominations

tr: identifying word or words by which someone or something is called and classified or distinguished from others
a class of one kind of unit in a system of numbers or measures or weights or money
example: he flashed a fistful of bills of large denominations

tr: a group of religious congregations having its own organization and a distinctive faith

value.def: A particular denomination is a particular religious group which has slightly different beliefs from other groups within the same faith.

example.ex: Acceptance of women preachers varies greatly from denomination to denomination.
example.tran: 在接受女性传教士的问题上，不同教派的态度大相径庭。

value.def: The denomination of a banknote or coin is its official value.

example.ex: ...a pile of bank notes, mostly in small denominations.
example.tran: 其中大部分都是小面额的一沓钞票
